title: $A lifts following US, Aust stocks
text:
Tue, Aug 11, 2015, 7:20 AM AEST - Australia Markets open in 2 hrs 40 mins $A lifts following US, Aust stocks AAP – 25 minutes ago Print 
The Australian dollar has risen a little, following a lift on Wall Street. 
At 0630 AEST on Tuesday, the currency was trading at 74.09 US cents, up from 73.90 cents on Monday. 
CURRENCY SNAPSHOT AT 0630 AEST ON TUESDAY 
One Australian dollar buys: 
* 74.09 US cents, from 73.90 cents on Monday 
* 92.31 Japanese yen, from 92 yen 
* 67.25 euro cents, from 67.41 euro cents 
(*Currency closes taken at 1700 AEST previous local session) 
Source: IRESS Australian market set to open higher AAP
